Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow for the hypertrack_live-app-android system:

```plantuml
@startuml hypertrack_live-app-android

actor User
participant "Android App" as App
participant CognitoClient
participant BackendClientFactory
participant AbstractBackendProvider
participant HyperTrackSDK
participant "Google Maps" as Maps
participant GeofenceApiAdapter

User -> App: Open app
App -> CognitoClient: Authenticate user
CognitoClient --> App: Authentication token

App -> BackendClientFactory: Create backend provider
BackendClientFactory --> App: AbstractBackendProvider instance

App -> AbstractBackendProvider: Create trip
AbstractBackendProvider -> HyperTrackSDK: Start tracking
HyperTrackSDK --> AbstractBackendProvider: Tracking started
AbstractBackendProvider --> App: Trip created

App -> Maps: Display user location
Maps --> App: Map view

User -> App: Set home location
App -> GeofenceApiAdapter: Create geofence
GeofenceApiAdapter --> App: Geofence created

User -> App: Share trip
App -> AbstractBackendProvider: Generate invite link
AbstractBackendProvider --> App: Invite link
App --> User: Display invite link

User -> App: End trip
App -> AbstractBackendProvider: Complete trip
AbstractBackendProvider -> HyperTrackSDK: Stop tracking
HyperTrackSDK --> AbstractBackendProvider: Tracking stopped
AbstractBackendProvider --> App: Trip completed

@enduml
```